From 40f98e8f7d13f286f3de553313bc12bf5ccab6fd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 00:49:45 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] regulator: mt6351: add regulator driver

Add support for the nine bucks and 30 unique LDO controls in the evidenced
MT6351 E2 revision. Select each buck active voltage register from its
hardware-control bit, preserve raw LDO selector ordering, and limit VPA to
its physical six-bit selector.

Do not expose the vendor framework duplicate VLDO28 alias or its invalid
VSRAM_PROC LDO entry. The descriptor table is mechanically checked against
the exact vendor register map and live MT6351 E2 state.

Signed-off-by: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/regulator/Kconfig                  |   9 +
 drivers/regulator/Makefile                 |   1 +
 drivers/regulator/mt6351-regulator.c       | 352 +++++++++++++++++++++
 include/linux/mfd/mt6351/registers.h       |  93 ++++++
 include/linux/regulator/mt6351-regulator.h |  48 +++
 5 files changed, 503 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/regulator/mt6351-regulator.c
 create mode 100644 include/linux/regulator/mt6351-regulator.h

